The is_empty method just returns whether there are any elements in queue2, which is the list of elements that have been dequeued. The peek method just returns the first element in either queue1 or queue2, depending on whether there are any elements in queue2.

This implementation of a queue using two stacks can be very efficient in terms of space and time, as it only uses two lists instead of one to store the elements. However, it requires more memory than a singly-linked list or a doubly-linked list implementation of a queue, as we need to store both the elements that are to be inserted and the elements that are to be removed.

